The paper deals with submodular optimization, which is a topic that falls under several sub-categories in computer science. The focus on optimization and machine learning applications suggests that cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) and cs.LG (Machine Learning) are likely categories. The use of submodular functions and combinatorial optimization suggests cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) as another possible category. The study of adaptivity and query complexity suggests cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.IT (Information Theory) as additional categories.
